OL,3,CUK retail sales remained flat as wet
OL,4,Cweather dampens food shopping
OL,6,FA fall in fuel sales, down 1.3%, was
OL,7,Fblamed on higher prices. These falls
OL,8,Fwere enough to offset the rise in
OL,9,Fsales volumes at clothing and
OL,10,Fdepartment stores, which were boosted
OL,11,Fby new collections.
OL,13,FOverall, non-food stores, which
OL,14,Finclude clothes sellers, saw their
OL,15,Fsales volumes increase by 1.7% during
OL,16,Fthe months.
